WEBVTT

00:03.770 --> 00:07.340
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>Everyone agrees that</i>
<i>one of the most important days</i>

00:07.374 --> 00:09.175
<i>of the year is Mother's Day.</i>

00:09.209 --> 00:11.177
ALL:
Happy Mother's Day!

00:11.211 --> 00:14.147
Oh, you guys
didn't have to do this.

00:14.180 --> 00:17.350
<i>Everybody wants to show their</i>
<i>mama how much they love them.</i>

00:17.384 --> 00:19.652
<i>Even Tupac</i>
<i>wrote a song about his mother.</i>

00:19.686 --> 00:23.156
<i>On Mother's Day,</i>
<i>people pull out all the stops.</i>

00:23.189 --> 00:25.425
<i>You take your mother</i>
<i>to brunch...</i>

00:25.458 --> 00:28.161
We're out of food.
I'm sorry for the inconvenience.

00:28.194 --> 00:29.829
If you could
come back next Sunday.

00:29.863 --> 00:31.731
What do you mean, next Sunday?

00:31.765 --> 00:34.100
We're out of food, Mama.
What you want me to do?

00:34.134 --> 00:36.536
Didn't I raise you
better than that?!

00:36.569 --> 00:40.440
<i>You take her to a movie so</i>
<i>she can wear a great big hat...</i>

00:40.473 --> 00:42.308
<i>and you spend</i>
<i>your last dime on her,</i>

00:42.342 --> 00:44.244
<i>just so she knows</i>
<i>she's number one.</i>

00:44.277 --> 00:46.479
Oh, my God! Ha-ha-ha!
Come on.

00:46.513 --> 00:50.850
Oh! Oh! Oh, I can't believe
you did this.

00:50.884 --> 00:54.320
<i>But when it comes to Father's</i>
<i>Day, nobody gave a damn.</i>

00:54.354 --> 00:55.855
It's Father's Day, people.

00:55.889 --> 00:57.691
Come on down
to Pastures and Shores.

00:57.724 --> 00:59.426
The food is half-price.

00:59.459 --> 01:02.862
<i>Buenas noches.</i>
<i>Â¿Como se dice</i>"half-off"?

01:02.896 --> 01:04.297
<i>The movies are terrible...</i>

01:04.330 --> 01:06.299
[ALL CLAMORING]

01:06.332 --> 01:09.302
Turn it off! Turn it off!

01:09.336 --> 01:10.870
<i>The gifts suck...</i>

01:10.904 --> 01:12.172
Ta-da!

01:12.205 --> 01:14.207
What the hell is this?

01:14.240 --> 01:15.642
It's a parking space, honey.

01:15.675 --> 01:18.778
We got you a parking space.

01:18.812 --> 01:21.748
<i>This year, I wanted to get</i>
<i>my father the perfect gift,</i>

01:21.781 --> 01:24.751
<i>and the only way to do that</i>
<i>was to ask him what he wanted.</i>

01:24.784 --> 01:27.887
Dad, what present
do you want for Father's Day?

01:27.921 --> 01:31.491
Heh-heh, wanna get me
something for Father's Day?

01:31.524 --> 01:33.493
Help me knock off
one of these bills.

01:33.526 --> 01:34.728
ROCHELLE:
Julius...

01:37.464 --> 01:38.865
Okay.

01:38.898 --> 01:40.200
Father's Day...

01:40.233 --> 01:42.669
You know what?

01:42.702 --> 01:45.472
Y'all really wanna get me
something for Father's Day?

01:45.505 --> 01:47.741
I know exactly what I want.
What's that, baby?

01:47.774 --> 01:49.442
A day off.

01:49.476 --> 01:52.645
You mean a day off from work?
No.

01:52.679 --> 01:55.849
A day off from everything
and everybody.

01:55.882 --> 01:58.818
No fighting, no shouting,

01:58.852 --> 02:01.321
no complaining, no fixing.

02:02.655 --> 02:06.192
Just one day where I can do
whatever I feel like doing.

02:06.226 --> 02:08.928
<i>I hope he doesn't want</i>
<i>to leave us for a white girl.</i>

02:08.962 --> 02:12.165
[***]

02:16.970 --> 02:19.339
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>

02:42.962 --> 02:45.799
[***]

02:45.832 --> 02:48.668
GREG:
So, wait, your dad says
he doesn't want anything?

02:48.702 --> 02:51.738
Nope. All he said was
he wanted to be all alone.

02:51.771 --> 02:54.607
Watch out. My mother said
she wanted a day alone.

02:54.641 --> 02:57.410
Next thing we knew, she left
and moved to Poughkeepsie.

02:57.444 --> 03:00.246
I don't care what he says.
I'm gonna get him something.

03:00.280 --> 03:01.548
<i>My father said what he wanted.</i>

03:01.581 --> 03:03.350
<i>My mother said</i>
<i>what he was gonna get.</i>

03:03.383 --> 03:05.719
What kind of gift is
a day off from your family?

03:05.752 --> 03:07.020
It's just one day.

03:07.053 --> 03:08.922
How is that supposed
to make the kids feel?

03:08.955 --> 03:10.890
<i>Women always used</i>
<i>the kids against you.</i>

03:10.924 --> 03:14.694
It's Father's Day and you
don't want to be a father.

03:14.728 --> 03:16.830
I did not say that.

03:16.863 --> 03:18.531
They're trying to honor you,

03:18.565 --> 03:21.301
and all you got to say is,
"Leave me the hell alone."

03:21.334 --> 03:23.503
I did not say,
"Leave me the hell alone."

03:23.536 --> 03:25.372
You may as well have.

03:25.405 --> 03:29.309
I haven't had a day
to myself in 13 years.

03:29.342 --> 03:31.511
If I didn't want
to be a father, I...

03:31.544 --> 03:33.546
<i>That look means if you want</i>
<i>to keep being a father</i>

03:33.580 --> 03:35.482
<i>you better</i>
<i>keep your mouth shut.</i>

03:35.515 --> 03:38.485
It is supposed to be our day
to do something special for you.

03:38.518 --> 03:41.654
That's what I'm trying to say.

03:41.688 --> 03:44.024
Why can't I do what
the hell I want to do?

03:44.057 --> 03:45.358
Huh? Say what?

03:45.392 --> 03:48.361
Uh... You got the keys?

03:49.863 --> 03:54.300
Well, what you gonna do here
all day by yourself anyway?

03:54.334 --> 03:55.669
Nothing.

03:55.702 --> 03:59.739
Well, can the kids at least
get you a real gift?

03:59.773 --> 04:01.341
What?

04:04.711 --> 04:06.613
What's that?
Every Father's Day card

04:06.646 --> 04:09.683
and present I've gotten
for the past four years.

04:09.716 --> 04:11.384
Look at this.

04:11.418 --> 04:12.952
A box of S-Curl.
I got you that.

04:12.986 --> 04:15.989
A macaroni cigar box.
Oh, that's so cute.

04:16.022 --> 04:22.462
I got four ties: a necktie
a bow tie, bolo tie...

04:22.495 --> 04:24.330
<i>I got him that.</i>

04:24.364 --> 04:25.999
...and a clip-on tie.

04:26.032 --> 04:28.835
I don't even wear ties.
I don't go nowhere.

04:32.439 --> 04:36.710
That's $28.46 we could have used
on something else.

04:36.743 --> 04:39.713
Well, it's the thought
that counts.

04:39.746 --> 04:43.516
I appreciate it, I really do,
but if you buy me presents,

04:43.550 --> 04:45.618
I'm just gonna have to work
to pay it off.

04:45.652 --> 04:48.521
At this rate,
I'll be working when I'm dead.

04:50.390 --> 04:52.092
Julius, you're dead.
What are you doing here?

04:52.125 --> 04:53.727
Trying to pay off
these presents.

04:53.760 --> 04:55.829
Listen, can I work
the graveyard shift?

04:57.964 --> 05:00.533
Fine. Okay, then.

05:00.567 --> 05:02.535
Have your little stinky day off.

05:02.569 --> 05:04.938
But on your birthday,
I will promise you this.

05:04.971 --> 05:06.439
You will be getting a cake,

05:06.473 --> 05:08.808
and you will like it.
Oh, I know.

05:08.842 --> 05:11.144
You better jump back
and kiss yourself.

05:11.177 --> 05:13.113
And, uh,
put up the groceries.

05:13.146 --> 05:15.448
Before your day off.

05:18.585 --> 05:20.553
Does he have any hobbies?

05:20.587 --> 05:23.656
Is taking naps a hobby?
No.

05:23.690 --> 05:25.959
So, what are you getting
your dad for Father's Day?

05:25.992 --> 05:28.862
I don't know if "getting" is
right. It's more like "doing."

05:28.895 --> 05:31.064
Okay, so, what are you
<i>doing</i>for your dad?

05:31.097 --> 05:34.434
Well, first, I'm making
his favorite breakfast,

05:34.467 --> 05:35.869
Cap'n Crunch and cantaloupe.

05:35.902 --> 05:37.570
<i>I tried to imagine</i>
<i>doing the things</i>

05:37.604 --> 05:39.606
<i>that Greg talked about</i>
<i>with my father.</i>

05:39.639 --> 05:42.008
<i>Like bringing him</i>
<i>Cap'n Crunch and cantaloupe.</i>

05:42.042 --> 05:43.610
Are you crazy?

05:43.643 --> 05:45.845
Boy, you better
bring me some bacon.

05:45.879 --> 05:49.482
<i>I thought about taking my dad</i>
<i>to the zoo to see penguins.</i>

05:49.516 --> 05:51.685
We paid $3.50 to see
a bird that can't fly?

05:51.718 --> 05:54.654
What you gonna show me next,
rats that don't eat cheese?

05:54.688 --> 05:57.123
<i>I even imagined us</i>
<i>shooting off bottle rockets</i>

05:57.157 --> 05:58.458
<i>in front of the house.</i>

05:58.491 --> 06:01.061
[ROCKET SHRIEKING]

06:01.094 --> 06:02.462
[BOOMING EXPLOSION]

06:02.495 --> 06:04.597
[GUNSHOTS]
[PEOPLE YELLING]

06:04.631 --> 06:05.932
Run, boy, run!

06:05.965 --> 06:08.902
<i>I wonder if Greg's dad</i>
<i>ever got shot at.</i>

06:10.770 --> 06:12.572
You decided
what you're gonna do?

06:12.605 --> 06:14.474
I can't do the stuff
you talked about.

06:14.507 --> 06:15.842
I only have $27.

06:15.875 --> 06:18.144
That's not bad.
If I were you, I'd figure out

06:18.178 --> 06:19.879
what he needs
and just give him that.

06:19.913 --> 06:22.115
<i>I wonder if it</i>
<i>would ruin our friendship</i>

06:22.148 --> 06:24.551
<i>if I smacked his eyebrows off?</i>

06:27.687 --> 06:29.989
What you looking for, Chris?

06:30.023 --> 06:33.560
Oh, I'm trying to find my father
something for Father's Day.

06:33.593 --> 06:35.195
Heh, Father's Day.

06:35.228 --> 06:37.831
My daddy liked
guns, liquor and women.

06:37.864 --> 06:39.799
<i>I guess he liked jail too.</i>

06:39.833 --> 06:41.935
What does your daddy
like to do?

06:41.968 --> 06:43.169
That's the tough part.

06:43.203 --> 06:45.638
All he does is sleep and work.

06:45.672 --> 06:49.909
I know what that's like.
But I got just the thing.

06:49.943 --> 06:54.948
A Swiss LCD quartz
calculator alarm watch.

06:54.981 --> 06:57.650
Well, he has
an alarm clock at home.

06:57.684 --> 06:59.185
What's he need one
in his watch for?

06:59.219 --> 07:00.653
You never know.

07:03.189 --> 07:04.924
[ALARM BEEPING]

07:04.958 --> 07:06.659
Oh!

07:06.693 --> 07:08.661
Thank goodness for this watch.

07:08.695 --> 07:10.764
Hm, I never thought of that.

07:10.797 --> 07:12.632
It's got a calculator too.

07:12.665 --> 07:14.801
He can figure out
how much<i>anything</i>costs.

07:14.834 --> 07:16.503
<i>If it came</i>
<i>with a side of bacon,</i>

07:16.536 --> 07:19.139
<i>that would have been</i>
<i>the best gift in history.</i>

07:19.172 --> 07:21.941
How much does it cost?

07:21.975 --> 07:23.510
Twenty-four ninety-five.

07:23.543 --> 07:25.045
<i>He just made that up.</i>
I'll take it.

07:28.248 --> 07:31.951
How come Daddy doesn't wanna
be with us on Father's Day?

07:31.985 --> 07:33.753
Oh, baby, it's not
that your daddy

07:33.787 --> 07:35.088
doesn't wanna be with us,

07:35.121 --> 07:37.157
it's just that
he works hard all the time

07:37.190 --> 07:39.793
and wants to have
a little time to be by himself.

07:39.826 --> 07:42.662
Man, that's cool.
I can't wait until I'm a father

07:42.696 --> 07:44.831
so I can have this
whole house to myself.

07:44.864 --> 07:47.100
You are not gonna be
a father in this house,

07:47.133 --> 07:50.203
because I ain't
taking care of no babies.

07:50.236 --> 07:51.671
Lost your mind.

07:51.705 --> 07:53.773
Well, can we still
get him a present?

07:53.807 --> 07:56.543
Sure, baby.
What'd you have in mind?

07:58.678 --> 08:01.848
These.
See, I took Daddy's old slippers

08:01.881 --> 08:03.817
and put macaroni on them.

08:03.850 --> 08:05.585
Oh, baby, that's nice.

08:05.618 --> 08:08.555
I'm gonna help you
wrap them later.

08:08.588 --> 08:10.090
Can you help me wrap mine too?

08:10.123 --> 08:11.658
I'm making dad cologne.

08:11.691 --> 08:13.660
Where did you learn
how to make cologne?

08:13.693 --> 08:15.729
I saw it in the back
of a magazine.

08:15.762 --> 08:17.330
All I need is oil,

08:17.364 --> 08:19.165
something to give it
a little smell

08:19.199 --> 08:20.600
and, uh, alcohol.

08:20.633 --> 08:22.135
Then just leave it
in a jar for a week.

08:22.168 --> 08:24.270
Mama, since Daddy
wants to be by himself,

08:24.304 --> 08:25.605
what are we gonna do?

08:25.638 --> 08:28.174
We are gonna have some fun.

08:28.208 --> 08:30.944
Chris! Time to eat!

08:33.013 --> 08:35.749
Hey, Dad, what's all that stuff?
It's a bunch of stuff

08:35.782 --> 08:38.151
guys on my route
got me for Father's Day.

08:38.184 --> 08:39.986
Oh, look at this.

08:40.020 --> 08:44.357
It's an LCD quartz
calculator alarm watch.

08:44.391 --> 08:46.993
It's the best gift I ever got.
Ha-ha!

08:47.027 --> 08:50.296
<i>Maybe I could glue some</i>
<i>macaroni to his shoes.</i>

08:50.330 --> 08:53.833
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

09:00.640 --> 09:03.743
[***]

09:03.777 --> 09:05.812
ALL:
Happy Father's Day!

09:05.845 --> 09:09.015
Happy Father's Day, baby.
We love you.

09:09.049 --> 09:13.219
Oh-ho-ho!
I love y'all too. Yeah.

09:13.253 --> 09:16.356
Hey, y'all have fun today, okay?

09:16.389 --> 09:18.792
Daddy, aren't you
gonna read your card?

09:18.825 --> 09:20.894
Ooh, yeah. Let's see here.

09:20.927 --> 09:22.629
Oh. Oh!

09:22.662 --> 09:24.764
[CHUCKLES]

09:24.798 --> 09:28.635
"To the best dad
in the whole world." Oh.

09:28.668 --> 09:30.170
That's so sweet.

09:30.203 --> 09:31.971
Oh, thank you.

09:32.005 --> 09:34.908
Y'all enjoy y'all selves
today, all right? Okay, bye-bye.

09:34.941 --> 09:37.177
Dad, we made your favorite
thing for breakfast.

09:37.210 --> 09:40.246
I brought your gout pills,
so you can eat without worrying.

09:40.280 --> 09:44.718
Oh, man, bacon, eggs with
cheese, biscuits and butter.

09:44.751 --> 09:46.653
I feel like I died
and went to heaven.

09:46.686 --> 09:48.722
Oh!
Thank you, baby.

09:48.755 --> 09:50.824
Oh, you're welcome, baby.
They did it all.

09:50.857 --> 09:52.759
When y'all leaving, huh?

09:52.792 --> 09:55.995
All right, in a minute.
And you're welcome.

09:56.029 --> 09:59.199
And, baby, make sure you take
those pills, okay?

09:59.232 --> 10:02.168
All right. You guys go
get ready so we can go.

10:02.202 --> 10:04.337
Hurry up, now. Hurry up. Faster.

10:04.371 --> 10:05.839
Isn't that sweet?
There you go.

10:05.872 --> 10:07.674
We have the best kids
in the world.

10:07.707 --> 10:09.075
Oh, yeah.
They're so sweet.

10:09.109 --> 10:11.044
They are.

10:11.077 --> 10:13.947
<i>That look means, "Ain't you</i>
<i>supposed to be leaving?"</i>

10:13.980 --> 10:15.949
You better hurry up. I mean...

10:15.982 --> 10:18.718
You're gonna be late for
your, uh... The, um, ahem...

10:18.752 --> 10:20.820
Uh, the...

10:20.854 --> 10:23.790
Uh, what y'all doing?
We're going to the museum.

10:23.823 --> 10:25.759
And to see the movie
<i>Trading Places.</i>

10:25.792 --> 10:27.694
Oh, that should be funny.
Right. Right.

10:27.727 --> 10:29.295
So you better hurry up,
all right?

10:29.329 --> 10:31.698
Okay, Julius, we're leaving.

10:31.731 --> 10:34.200
Well, I'll be home
in time for dinner, okay?

10:34.234 --> 10:35.802
Thank you. I love you.

10:35.835 --> 10:37.971
I love you too, baby.
Thank you.

10:39.406 --> 10:41.908
You have a good day.
All right. Oh, I will.

10:41.941 --> 10:44.277
Get on out of here.
Happy Father's Day!

10:44.310 --> 10:45.779
Hey, enjoy yourself.
I will.

10:45.812 --> 10:47.280
<i>For my father to have one day</i>

10:47.313 --> 10:49.716
<i>where he could do</i>
<i>whatever he felt like doing</i>

10:49.749 --> 10:52.085
<i>was like finding</i>
<i>a million dollars.</i>

10:55.288 --> 10:56.423
[***]

11:02.195 --> 11:04.798
<i>He slept on the couch.</i>

11:04.831 --> 11:08.001
<i>He slept in the bed.</i>

11:08.034 --> 11:09.936
<i>He slept</i>
<i>on the dining room table</i>

11:09.969 --> 11:12.005
<i>and dreamt his favorite dreams.</i>

11:12.038 --> 11:15.275
Seventeen cent worth of butter.

11:15.308 --> 11:17.477
<i>He watched bowling.</i>

11:17.510 --> 11:18.478
Yeah!

11:18.511 --> 11:20.280
Ha-ha-ha! Yes!

11:20.313 --> 11:22.515
<i>He watched baseball.</i>
ANNOUNCER:<i>Here's the pitch.</i>

11:22.549 --> 11:24.150
<i>It's gone!</i>
Yeah!

11:24.184 --> 11:25.852
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>He watched golf.</i>

11:25.885 --> 11:27.520
ANNOUNCER:
<i>On it's way, and it's in.</i>

11:27.554 --> 11:30.023
Oh-ho-ho, yeah!

11:30.056 --> 11:35.061
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>He even did stuff we didn't</i>
<i>know he did, like painting.</i>

11:35.095 --> 11:36.896
<i>While my father</i>
<i>was doing things</i>

11:36.930 --> 11:38.898
<i>he wouldn't do</i>
<i>while we were around,</i>

11:38.932 --> 11:40.900
<i>we were doing things</i>
<i>we wouldn't do</i>

11:40.934 --> 11:42.102
<i>while he was around.</i>

11:42.135 --> 11:44.771
Okay, y'all stay
where I can see you.

11:44.804 --> 11:46.539
All right, now,
you sure about this?

11:46.573 --> 11:48.942
Mr. Harris gave me
my money back on the watch,

11:48.975 --> 11:52.278
so I wanted to see if I can
find Dad something he'll like.

11:52.312 --> 11:54.280
Okay. But gift or no gift,

11:54.314 --> 11:56.816
if you're not home by 6:30,
I'm calling the police.

11:56.850 --> 11:59.853
<i>My mother always told us</i>
<i>if we weren't home on time,</i>

11:59.886 --> 12:02.288
<i>she was calling the police.</i>

12:02.322 --> 12:04.124
Here.
What's this?

12:04.157 --> 12:05.792
Oh, it's money
I was gonna use

12:05.825 --> 12:07.827
to buy a gift for your dad.
Thanks.

12:07.861 --> 12:09.929
You're welcome, baby.
Be careful.

12:09.963 --> 12:11.998
<i>The only thing tougher</i>
<i>than finding a gift</i>

12:12.032 --> 12:13.500
<i>for the man that has everything</i>

12:13.533 --> 12:16.770
<i>is finding one for the man</i>
<i>that wants nothing.</i>

12:18.304 --> 12:20.240
<i>The only time</i>
<i>my father wore a suit</i>

12:20.273 --> 12:24.310
<i>was at funerals, graduations</i>
<i>and on laundry day.</i>

12:24.344 --> 12:26.413
<i>The closest</i>
<i>my father got to jewelry</i>

12:26.446 --> 12:28.448
<i>was listening to Neil Diamond.</i>

12:28.481 --> 12:31.518
<i>I hope it lasts</i>
<i>as long as the payments.</i>

12:32.986 --> 12:35.021
<i>I wasn't sure</i>
<i>if he would feed the rabbit,</i>

12:35.055 --> 12:37.123
<i>or use the rabbit to feed us.</i>

12:37.157 --> 12:39.993
<i>And let's just say</i>
<i>he wasn't the leg warmer type.</i>

12:42.328 --> 12:45.131
<i>While I was trying to figure</i>
<i>out what to get my father,</i>

12:45.165 --> 12:46.933
<i>my mother was trying</i>
<i>to figure out</i>

12:46.966 --> 12:49.536
<i>what she had gotten</i>
<i>herself into.</i>

12:51.171 --> 12:53.273
What is that?

12:53.306 --> 12:56.309
Well, honey, that's art.

12:56.343 --> 12:58.845
You sure?
Looks like somebody got shot

12:58.878 --> 13:00.380
and fell in a bucket
of mustard.

13:00.413 --> 13:02.415
Be quiet, boy.

13:02.449 --> 13:04.084
This is culture.

13:04.117 --> 13:06.252
How much more culture
do we have to get?

13:06.286 --> 13:08.888
Girl, just look
at the picture.

13:09.889 --> 13:11.391
[GROUP CHATTERING]

13:11.424 --> 13:13.159
[CHILD LAUGHS]

13:15.995 --> 13:17.530
I wish Dad was here.

13:17.564 --> 13:19.299
Maybe he  could explain this.

13:24.104 --> 13:25.505
Hey, Risky?
Hold up, little man.

13:25.538 --> 13:27.874
<i>I had looked for a gift</i>
<i>everywhere I could,</i>

13:27.907 --> 13:30.477
<i>so I decided to look</i>
<i>somewhere I shouldn't have.</i>

13:30.510 --> 13:33.079
What kind of stuff
do you have for Father's Day?

13:33.113 --> 13:35.415
Father's Day?
That ain't a big one for me.

13:35.448 --> 13:38.218
There ain't none but four
fathers in the neighborhood.

13:38.251 --> 13:41.488
Now, Mother's Day, I had
a whole bunch of stuff.

13:41.521 --> 13:44.157
How much you got to spend?
Thirty-seven dollars.

13:44.190 --> 13:46.659
Thirty-seven dollars?
You knock over a liquor store?

13:46.693 --> 13:48.461
I saved up.
Man,

13:48.495 --> 13:50.964
keep saving like that,
you'll be rich in a minute.

13:50.997 --> 13:54.000
<i>Maybe then I can buy one of</i>
<i>those pink sweaters, like him.</i>

13:54.034 --> 13:56.302
Your old man like music?
Who's that?

13:56.336 --> 13:57.904
Oh.

13:57.937 --> 13:59.139
We got John Travolta,

13:59.172 --> 14:02.175
William Shatner.
Oh! Liberace.

14:02.208 --> 14:05.278
<i>That's for fathers that were</i>
<i>too old for Elton John.</i>

14:05.311 --> 14:08.314
No, thanks.
What else you got?

14:08.348 --> 14:10.016
Uh... Oh!

14:10.050 --> 14:12.185
How about these... for your mom?

14:12.218 --> 14:15.655
For Father's Day?
Yeah. For him to give to her.

14:15.689 --> 14:17.323
No.

14:17.357 --> 14:21.027
Uh, I'm sorry I can't
help you out, young blood,

14:21.061 --> 14:23.697
but, hey, you come back
Mother's Day, I'll hook you up.

14:23.730 --> 14:25.465
Listen, watch this
for a few minutes.

14:25.498 --> 14:28.268
I'm gonna run across the street,
pay my light bill. All right?

14:28.301 --> 14:29.336
Sure.

14:29.369 --> 14:32.505
Tell your daddy to call me
and happy Father's Day.

14:32.539 --> 14:37.444
<i>Back at home, my father still</i>
<i>had the house to himself...</i>

14:37.477 --> 14:39.713
Rochelle?

14:39.746 --> 14:41.047
Chris?

14:41.081 --> 14:42.482
<i>...whether he liked it or not.</i>

14:42.515 --> 14:45.085
ANNOUNCER:
<i>And if you order now,</i>

14:45.118 --> 14:47.387
<i>you'll get this set</i>
<i>of microwavable...</i>

14:47.420 --> 14:49.556
MAN:
<i>In the city</i>
<i>that never sleeps...</i>

14:49.589 --> 14:52.625
WOMAN:
<i>Psychic Station</i>
<i>TV Network...</i>

14:52.659 --> 14:55.528
MAN:
<i>This proud father goose</i>
<i>is no exception.</i>

14:55.562 --> 14:58.531
<i>He graciously watches over</i>
<i>and protects his chicks,</i>

14:58.565 --> 15:01.101
<i>assuring their safety</i>
<i>until they are old enough</i>

15:01.134 --> 15:03.136
<i>to fend for themselves.</i>

15:03.169 --> 15:05.572
<i>In the wild, babies are</i>
<i>almost never abandoned</i>

15:05.605 --> 15:08.675
<i>and rarely left alone for</i>
<i>any extended period of time.</i>

15:08.708 --> 15:10.410
CHRIS ROCK:
<i>A great man once said,</i>

15:10.443 --> 15:13.046
<i>"Nothing screams louder</i>
<i>than the sound of silence."</i>

15:13.079 --> 15:15.181
<i>I think it was Nipsy Russell.</i>

15:16.282 --> 15:19.419
Thank you. Enjoy your show.

15:19.452 --> 15:22.322
Hi. Um, can I have
one adult, two children

15:26.026 --> 15:28.094
You<i>must</i>think I'm a fool.

15:28.128 --> 15:30.063
You want me to believe
he's under 12?

15:30.096 --> 15:32.632
JULIUS:
Yeah, she does.

15:32.665 --> 15:34.401
TONYA: Daddy!
DREW: Dad!

15:34.434 --> 15:36.136
ROCHELLE:
What are you doing here?

15:36.169 --> 15:38.204
I missed you guys.

15:38.238 --> 15:40.140
Father's Day
without your family...

15:40.173 --> 15:43.009
it's like not being a father.

15:43.043 --> 15:44.611
<i>That look means,</i>

15:44.644 --> 15:47.547
<i>"That's what I was trying</i>
<i>to tell your stupid ass!"</i>

15:47.580 --> 15:49.049
Come here.

15:50.450 --> 15:53.153
Where's Chris?
Oh, he went to buy you a gift.

15:53.186 --> 15:55.555
But I told...
Julius, please, just promise me

15:55.588 --> 15:59.526
you will act like it's the best
gift you've ever gotten.

15:59.559 --> 16:01.761
I promise.
All right.

16:01.795 --> 16:03.196
All right.

16:03.229 --> 16:05.532
Uh, that'll be two kids,
two adults

16:05.565 --> 16:09.035
for, uh,<i>Trading Places.</i>

16:09.069 --> 16:11.071
There you go.
What's this?

16:11.104 --> 16:13.640
Father's Day special,
two for one.

16:13.673 --> 16:15.342
[REGISTER BEEPING]

16:19.112 --> 16:21.047
Happy Father's Day, Daddy.

16:21.081 --> 16:22.449
I made these for you.

16:22.482 --> 16:24.317
I know you said
don't get you a gift,

16:24.351 --> 16:27.087
but I wanted something
in case you changed your mind.

16:27.120 --> 16:31.291
Oh! Macaroni-covered
slippers! Ha-ha!

16:31.324 --> 16:34.461
It goes with the macaroni
cigar box I got last year.

16:34.494 --> 16:35.395
I know.

16:37.097 --> 16:38.665
Dad, I got something
for you too.

16:38.698 --> 16:40.367
Oh, what's this?

16:41.634 --> 16:43.470
A bottle of iodine?

16:43.503 --> 16:45.605
No, no, no, it's cologne.
I made it myself.

16:45.638 --> 16:48.241
I just couldn't find
a bottle to put it in,

16:48.274 --> 16:50.610
so I poured the iodine out
and put it in there.

16:50.643 --> 16:52.812
Boy, that iodine cost 99...

16:52.846 --> 16:54.180
[CLEARS THROAT]

16:56.182 --> 16:58.151
[DOOR OPENS]
[SNIFFS]

16:58.184 --> 17:00.153
Mm, that smells good.

17:00.186 --> 17:02.655
Ha-ha, thank you, Drew.
ROCHELLE: Oh, that's nice.

17:02.689 --> 17:04.624
Oh, man, thank you so much.
Chris?

17:04.657 --> 17:07.093
You know I was about
to call the police, right?

17:07.127 --> 17:08.628
Hey, Chris, where you been?

17:08.661 --> 17:11.498
I was trying to find you
a gift for Father's Day.

17:11.531 --> 17:12.699
[MOUTHING WORDS]

17:12.732 --> 17:14.634
Well, I'm sure whatever you got,

17:14.668 --> 17:16.136
it's fine.

17:16.169 --> 17:17.637
That's the thing.
I looked all over,

17:17.671 --> 17:21.241
but I couldn't find you anything
I thought you would like.

17:21.274 --> 17:23.376
Doesn't matter.
It's the thought that counts.

17:23.410 --> 17:25.545
So did you find something?

17:25.578 --> 17:27.313
Not really.

17:27.347 --> 17:29.516
It's more of,
I did something for you.

17:29.549 --> 17:31.851
[***]

17:36.723 --> 17:40.427
What? What is it?

17:40.460 --> 17:42.128
It's a receipt.

17:42.162 --> 17:43.797
He paid the electric bill.

17:43.830 --> 17:47.467
Oh, baby, that is so...

17:47.500 --> 17:49.703
CHRIS:
When I asked if I
could get you anything,

17:49.736 --> 17:52.472
you said I could help you
knock out a bill.

17:52.505 --> 17:55.208
That was the only one
I could afford.

17:56.476 --> 17:58.411
Thanks, son.

17:58.445 --> 18:01.247
<i>My father never really cared</i>
<i>much about presents,</i>

18:01.281 --> 18:03.416
<i>but giving him a reason</i>
<i>to smile</i>

18:03.450 --> 18:05.552
<i>was the best thing</i>
<i>I could ever do for him.</i>

18:05.585 --> 18:08.588
This is the best gift
I ever got.

18:08.621 --> 18:12.759
I'll remember this forever.
Happy Father's Day.

18:12.792 --> 18:14.160
I'm proud of you, Chris.

18:14.194 --> 18:16.262
Becoming more
of a man every day.

18:16.296 --> 18:17.697
Thanks, Dad.

18:17.731 --> 18:19.265
You know, I was thinking,

18:19.299 --> 18:21.368
it might be a good idea
if you get a job

18:21.401 --> 18:23.336
and start paying a bill
every month.

18:23.370 --> 18:27.674
<i>* Everybody hates Chris </i>

18:31.378 --> 18:34.481
<i>Stay tuned for scenes</i>
<i>from our next episode.</i>

18:36.783 --> 18:40.220
[***]

18:40.253 --> 18:43.223
<i>* Aw, make it funky now </i>
